SPEECH,
OR
COMPLAINT,
LATELY
Made by the Spanish Embassadour to his Ma-
jestie at Oxford, upon occasion of the taking of a
Ship called Sancta Clara in the Port of Sancto Domingo,
richly laden with Plate, Cocheneal and other
commodities of great value,
By one Captaine Bennet Strafford, and by
Him brought to Southampton.
Being a matter of high concernment betwixt the
two Kings of Spaine and England
Also a Proclamation prohibiting the buying or
disposing of any the lading of the ship called the
Sancta Clara, lately brought into Southampton.
Translated out of the Spanish, in Oxford,
BY
Sr Torriano, an Italian.
LONDON,
Printed for Nathaniel Butter, Jan. 17. 1643.
